Hughes Storm and Associates - Roy F. Hughes


















 













Home Attorneys  Roy F. Hughes


Our Attorneys



Roy F. Hughes
Partner  (808) 526-9744 Ext. 104
After graduating from Punahou School, Mr. Hughes moved to Wisconsin where he attended Ripon College and received his J.D. from Marquette University Law School. He began his own practice in 1987.

Mr. Hughes' career focus is in insurance defense, the defense of insurance companies and their policyholders in litigation matters, including mediation, arbitration, trials and appeals. He has defended automobile, premises, product and sports injury claims, insurance coverage matters, including drafting of exclusionary endorsements, complex construction defect claims, real estate and legal errors and omissions claims. 

Mr. Hughes is actively involved in mediations and arbitrations through Dispute Prevention & Resolutions (DPR) in the State of Hawaii.
 
Mr. Hughes participated in the briefing and arguments in the following reported Hawaii cases:



Doherty v Hartford Insurance, 58 Haw. 570 (1978)
Brown v Clark Equipment, 62 Haw. 530 (1980)
King v 1/ikai Properties, 2 Haw. App. 359 (1981)
Peters v Peters, 63 Haw. 653 (1981)
Socal v Hawaiian Insurance & Guranty Co., 65 Haw. 521 (1982)
Lim v Harvis Construction Co., 65 Haw. 71 (1982)
Kaneko v Hilo Coast Processing, 65 Haw 447 (1982)
Alt v Krueger, 4 Haw. App. 201 (1983)
Sturla v Firemans Fund Insurance Co., 67 Haw. 203 (1984)
Rana v Bishop Insurance Co., 6 Haw. App. 1 (1985)
Commerce & Industry Ins. Co. v Bank of Hawaii, 73 Haw. (1992)
Pacific International Services Corp. v Hurip, 76 Haw. 209 (1994)
Dun/ea v Dappen, 83 Haw. 28 (1996)
Island Insurance Co. v Johnny's Plumbing, 86 Haw. 363 (1997)
Tradewind Insurance Co. v Bayudan, 87 Haw. App. 379 (1998)
Island Insurance Co. v Dairy Road Partners, 92 Haw. 398 (2000)
Nautilus Insurance Co. v Lexington Insurance Co., 132 Haw. 283 (2014)

 
 


